snippet: Adam LaRoche hit his career-high 33rd home run Tuesday, making him the third Washington Nationals player to drive in 100 runs in a season.
abstract: Baseball Roundup; Washington Nationals defeat the Philadelphia Phillies, 4-2; Nationals first baseman Adam LaRoche hits his career-high 33rd home run, making him the third Nationals player to drive in 100 runs in a season; other scores noted.
lead_paragraph: Adam LaRoche hit his career-high 33rd home run Tuesday, making him the third Washington Nationals player to drive in 100 runs in a season.
